reviews.review_description:
Syberia is one of top 3 games I always wanted to see in VR, but this is not really it. If it was some free fan VR remake, issues would be understandable, but you want money for this, yet it lacks testing finishing, polish, and its not even in Early Access or Beta.

There is many downsides to this VR implementation, to mention just few:
lack of smooth turning, step turning includes blackscreen blink even when blink time is at 0; 
seated mode or even standing mode is bad, since some objects have the white interaction orb above them so you can pick them from "standing" height (cogs) yet others lack the white orbs, so you have to pick them up almost from ground (the tool for factory gate) 
the walking and running is too slow - this is the first game where I voluntarily use teleport most of the time;
with phone I naturally extended just the index finger to press the buttons, but button were not usable, and I got stuck on it for a while, only when I extended all fingers and reached to the phone, the game folded my fingers to press the buttons just with index, super unintuitive;
the highlighted interactions would be cool, if all were highlighted, now it just makes the game quite confusing with interactions that are not highlighted (to switch off the highlights would be neat); 
the reader on documents lacks some in game way to toggle it on & off.

The graphics are a big issue, heavy aliasing even on loadscreens. The blur everywhere with no option to turn it off. Compared to the 2002 original the graphics looks much worse, if there was PCVR version with decent graphics, I would be praising here that you made the Quest port run so well, but Quest version being the only VR choice, its just bad, and the hardware limitation does not excuse it, when its deliberate decision. You could have make it look good, or even include VR support in the PC Remastered version, but you rather chose to make it like this. I would say its even insult to name of Benoit Sokal.
